<item>
            <title>[QPIDJMS-301] Pooled Buffer leak possible on send when connection has dropped</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/QPIDJMS-301</link>
                <project id="12314524" key="QPIDJMS">Qpid JMS</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;For an in-progress send that hits the transport level after the connection has dropped the outbound buffer can remain reference counted and not released if a pooled buffer allocator is in use.  This could cause long term issues in cases where failover transport is used and the application remains up for a long time, or when the application creates new connections and recovers on connection loss.  &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
